ons\":[[],{\"s\":\"arr\"}],\"mountedInfolistActionsData\":[[],{\"s\":\"arr\"}],\"mountedInfolistActionsComponent\":null,\"mountedInfolistActionsInfolist\":null,\"isTableLoaded\":false,\"tableRecordsPerPage\":10,\"tableColumnSearches\":[[],{\"s\":\"arr\"}],\"toggledTableColumns\":[{\"sample_id\":true},{\"s\":\"arr\"}],\"mountedTableActions\":[[\"view\",\"recommend\"],{\"s\":\"arr\"}],\"mountedTableActionsData\":[[[[],{\"s\":\"arr\"}],[{\"validation_status\":null,\"expert_comments\":\"SOIL ANALYSIS RECOMMENDATION REPORT\\nSource: Bureau of Soils & Water Management (BSWM) \\\/ FAO Soil Interpretation Guidelines\\n==========================================================================================\\nCrop     : Arabica\\nSoil Type: Sandy Loam\\n==========================================================================================\\n\\n1. SOIL CONDITION ASSESSMENT\\n+----------------------+------------+-----------+------------------------------------------------------+\\n| Parameter            | Value      | Rating    | Remarks                                              |\\n+----------------------+------------+-----------+------------------------------------------------------+\\n| Soil pH              | 1.5        | Very Low  | Extremely acidic. Fix FIRST before fertilizing.      |\\n| Organic Matter       | 2.1%       | Moderate  | Adequate. Maintain with 2-3 t\\\/ha compost\\\/yr.         |\\n| Nitrogen (N)         | 0.1%       | Low       | Deficient. Apply 60-90 kg N\\\/ha in 2 splits.          |\\n| Phosphorus (P)       | 15 ppm     | Medium    | Adequate. Maintenance dose 20-40 kg P2O5\\\/ha.         |\\n| Potassium (K)        | 200 ppm    | Medium    | Adequate. Maintenance dose 20-40 kg K2O\\\/ha.          |\\n+----------------------+------------+-----------+------------------------------------------------------+\\n\\n2. FERTILIZER RECOMMENDATION\\n   (Note: full application timing is in Section 4 below)\\n+-----------------+--------------------------------------+--------------------+----------------------+\\n| Nutrient        | Fertilizer Product                   | Rate (per ha)      | When to Apply        |\\n+-----------------+--------------------------------------+--------------------+----------------------+\\n| Nitrogen (N)    | Urea (46-0-0) or Complete Fert. (14- | 60-90 kg N\\\/ha      | Split 2x (see Sec. 4 |\\n| Phosphorus (P)  | Solophos (0-18-0)                    | 20-40 kg P2O5\\\/ha   | At planting (maint.) |\\n| Potassium (K)   | Muriate of Potash (0-0-60)           | 20-40 kg K2O\\\/ha    | At planting (maint.) |\\n+-----------------+--------------------------------------+--------------------+----------------------+\\n\\n3. SOIL AMENDMENT\\n+------------------------+------------------------------------+--------------+--------------------------+\\n| Concern                | Product                            | Rate         | When to Apply            |\\n+------------------------+------------------------------------+--------------+--------------------------+\\n| pH Correction (Acidic) | Agricultural Lime (CaCO3)          | 2-4 t\\\/ha     | NOW \\u2014 before fertilizing |\\n| Organic Matter (Mainta | Compost                            | 2-3 t\\\/ha     | Annually to maintain     |\\n+------------------------+------------------------------------+--------------+--------------------------+\\n\\n4. APPLICATION SCHEDULE SUMMARY\\n+----------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------+\\n| When                       | Action \\\/ What to Do                                                  |\\n+----------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------+\\n| IMMEDIATELY                | Apply Agricultural Lime to correct acidic soil pH.                   |\\n| After 2-4 weeks            | Apply compost and fertilizers (after lime has worked).               |\\n| Every planting season      | Apply compost or organic matter to build soil health.                |\\n| At planting                | Apply phosphorus fertilizer near root zone (banded).                 |\\n| At planting (basal)        | Apply 50% of nitrogen + 50% of potassium fertilizer.                 |\\n| 1-2 months after planting  | Apply remaining 50% nitrogen + remaining 50% potassium (top-dress).  |\\n| Every year                 | Apply organic matter (compost\\\/manure) to maintain soil health.       |\\n| Every 6-12 months          | Re-test soil to evaluate progress and update fertilizer plan.        |\\n+----------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------+\\n\\n5. GOOD FARMING PRACTICES\\n  * Mulch around coffee plants with dried leaves or rice straw (5-10 cm thick).\\n  * Keep crop residues on the field after harvest -- do NOT burn them.\\n  * Plant legume cover crops during fallow season to naturally add nitrogen.\\n  * Avoid deep plowing to protect soil structure and organic matter.\\n  * Never apply fertilizer on extremely dry or waterlogged soil.\\n  * Always wash hands after handling fertilizers and chemicals.\\n\\n==========================================================================================\\nIMPORTANT REMINDERS\\n==========================================================================================\\n  ! ALWAYS correct soil pH FIRST -- fertilizers do not work on wrong pH.\\n  ! SPLIT nitrogen and potassium -- never apply the full dose at once.\\n  ! RE-TEST your soil every 6-12 months after major amendments.\\n  ! BANDED application of phosphorus near roots is more efficient than broadcasting.\\n==========================================================================================\"},{\"s\":\"arr\"}]],{\"s\":\"arr\"}],\"mountedTableActionsArguments\":[[[[],{\"s\":\"arr\"}],[[],{\"s\":\"arr\"}]],{\"s\":\"arr\"}],\"mountedTableActionRecord\":\"1\",\"defaultTableAction\":null,\"defaultTableActionArguments\":null,\"defaultTableActionRec